description.narrative:
The proposed activities aim to develop cutting-edge knowledge and evidence-based policy and technical guidelines that constitute good practices for the financial inclusion of rural youth and sustainable agri-finance to inform the work of the community of practice and CABFIN beneficiaries. More specifically, the objective will be to develop the following expected products:

1) A collection of case studies on selected applications of green finance instruments and approaches in the agriculture and food sectors with a focus on promoting access to green finance for smallholder farmers;
2) Technical guidance material on country-level assessments of financial markets for rural green finance products and services;
3) A policy brief on creating conducive enabling conditions for youth-focused agri-finance at country level.
